  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "25-29. as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him—a mark of the highest respect.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "fell down at his feet, and worshipped him—In the East this way of showing respect was customary not only to kings, but to others occupying a superior station; but among the Greeks and Romans it was reserved for the gods. Peter, therefore, declines it as due to no mortal [Grotius]. \"Those who claim to have succeeded Peter, have not imitated this part of his conduct\" [Alford] (therein only verifying 2Th 2:4, and compare Re 19:10; 22:9).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
