  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And as he talked with him,.... About the excessive respect he showed him, and his own infirmity and frailty, and unworthiness, as a creature: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he went in; to Cornelius's house, at the door, and through the porch, to some interior room and apartment in it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and found many that were come together; besides his family, many of his relations and intimate friends, whom he had got together on this occasion, that they might receive some advantage, as well as himself. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and found many that were come together; besides his family, many of his relations and intimate friends, whom he had got together on this occasion, that they might receive some advantage, as well as himself. ",
            "children": []
